Since $x$ and $\lfloor x\rfloor$ are both positive, they are both greater than $0$.  This means we can safely multiply them to find that $x\cdot\lfloor x\rfloor=70$.  Since $x\cdot\lfloor x\rfloor=70$, $x=\dfrac{70}{\lfloor x\rfloor}$.  $x$ is positive, so we know that $x>\lfloor x\rfloor$.  Thus, $x=\dfrac{70}{\lfloor x\rfloor}<70$.

Since $10\le x<11$ (for example), $\lfloor x\rfloor=10$, and $x=\dfrac{70}{10}=\boxed{7}$.
